1
00:00:26,600 --> 00:00:28,520
Come on, dear. Wake up.

2
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,680
Teacher.

3
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:51,880
- Yes, honey ?
- I can't do this question.

4
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:55,440
OK, let's see what it says.

5
00:01:55,760 --> 00:02:02,400
Which one of the following
statements is correct ?

6
00:02:04,440 --> 00:02:07,880
NOAH LAND

7
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:13,360
Unlock it, son, will you ?

8
00:04:13,720 --> 00:04:15,720
- It's already unlocked.
- Really ?

9
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:26,200
It does that sometimes.
There is a problem with the switch.

10
00:04:26,680 --> 00:04:28,600
Sit in the back for now.
I'll fix it later.

11
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:51,520
Here.

12
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:53,640
Some chocolate.

13
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:55,480
- What's that ?
- Chocolate.

14
00:04:55,760 --> 00:04:58,160
No, thanks. Not now.
Put it down there.

15
00:07:29,440 --> 00:07:30,920
- Who is it ?
- It's me, son.

16
00:07:37,160 --> 00:07:38,720
What's going on ?

17
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:41,520
What ? Are you in pain ?

18
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:44,640
- Didn't you bring your pills ?
- Can you take me for a drive ?

19
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:48,280
A drive ? We can go to
hospital if you like.

20
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:52,160
No. Fresh air and
a change of scene will help.

21
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:54,640
Are you sure ?
You don't look good.

22
00:07:56,440 --> 00:07:58,240
OK, fine.
I'll be right out.

23
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:09,760
What's going on ?
Why the crowds ?

24
00:09:20,720 --> 00:09:22,000
Stop up ahead there.

25
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:23,520
- You want me to stop ?
- Yes.

26
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:27,200
Stop, stop. Just here.

27
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:32,480
Where are we ?

28
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:35,080
I think I know.

29
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:41,040
This is the road up to our land.

30
00:09:50,240 --> 00:09:52,920
What is this ? Why have we stopped ?
What's going on ?

31
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:56,640
- It's the road to our land.
- What ?

32
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:58,760
Yes, it's the road. Follow me.

33
00:10:22,160 --> 00:10:25,000
- Water ! Cold water !
- Cold water !

34
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:45,600
Who are you ?

35
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:54,600
Who are you ?

36
00:12:57,400 --> 00:12:59,640
Who are you ?

37
00:13:01,360 --> 00:13:02,960
Who are you ? Come with me.

38
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:06,200
Let's find you some food.
He's some kind of purebred.

39
00:13:20,680 --> 00:13:21,960
Selam aleykum.

40
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:24,840
- Aleykum selam.
- Aleykum selam, Uncle.

41
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:26,720
How are you, honey ?

42
00:13:26,880 --> 00:13:29,680
Turn that toaster off.
Someone's left it on.

43
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:37,120
How are we doing, lads ?
How many pilgrims today ?

44
00:13:37,240 --> 00:13:38,720
1896, Uncle.

45
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:40,560
Praise God !

46
00:13:41,880 --> 00:13:44,720
Clear up this lot.
It looks bad for customers.

47
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:46,520
- Hello.
- Aleykum selam.

48
00:13:46,680 --> 00:13:49,080
I'll have these.
It's Cevdet, isn't it ?

49
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:52,680
- Yes.
- I'm the son of Aziz Karamusa.

50
00:13:53,440 --> 00:13:55,040
My name's Ibrahim.

51
00:13:55,560 --> 00:13:57,480
Karamusa... Ah, yes.

52
00:13:59,440 --> 00:14:01,600
- What can I do for you ?
- We arrived yesterday.

53
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:03,120
I know. I heard.

54
00:14:03,200 --> 00:14:05,000
I'm a sick man.
My days are numbered.

55
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:07,960
No ! May God heal you !
Where there's God, there's hope.

56
00:14:08,560 --> 00:14:10,840
- How can I help ?
- My son's here with me.

57
00:14:11,160 --> 00:14:14,200
I want to be buried
under the tree I planted as a boy.

58
00:14:14,360 --> 00:14:16,000
That's why my son came.

59
00:14:16,240 --> 00:14:18,520
Take your pick.
The trees belong to God.

60
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:20,600
Those old feuds are history.

61
00:14:20,760 --> 00:14:22,000
- Well...
- Forget the past.

62
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:25,720
- The tree on the hill.
- What, the poplar on Hoca Hill ?

63
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:28,120
No. The one everyone visits.

64
00:14:31,920 --> 00:14:34,080
- The Noah Tree.
- That's the one.

65
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:37,120
- Yes ?
- I planted that tree.

66
00:14:38,680 --> 00:14:41,760
- God forgive you !
- Someone's put up a prayer room there.

67
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:43,920
A fence, too.

68
00:14:44,400 --> 00:14:48,120
Here's the title deed.
You can keep it. I have the original.

69
00:14:48,240 --> 00:14:49,400
What are you talking about ?

70
00:14:49,480 --> 00:14:51,640
If you'd clean up all the stakes
and ribbons there...

71
00:14:51,720 --> 00:14:53,240
That tree is 4 000 years old.

72
00:14:53,320 --> 00:14:55,440
- I'd appreciate it.
- Wait a second.

73
00:14:57,120 --> 00:14:59,720
-What do you want with this Noah tree ?
- It's OK, it's nothing.

74
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:02,960
- Dad, I... Can we go outside ?
- Do you mind ?

75
00:15:03,120 --> 00:15:04,960
- Dad, I...
- Do you mind ?

76
00:15:05,280 --> 00:15:08,840
Now, that tree is 49 years old,
not 4 000.

77
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:11,400
If you don't believe me,
count the age rings.

78
00:15:11,520 --> 00:15:14,560
The tree doesn't age.
But what do you know about miracles ?

79
00:15:14,640 --> 00:15:18,560
- Uncle, let me get rid of them.
- Take it easy. Sit down there.

80
00:15:19,640 --> 00:15:21,200
Young fellow.

81
00:15:21,880 --> 00:15:25,640
Take your father away. What
you're doing is a sin. Shame on you.

82
00:15:25,720 --> 00:15:28,040
No, shame on you.
I planted that tree.

83
00:15:28,160 --> 00:15:30,240
No ! The Prophet Noah planted it.

84
00:15:30,320 --> 00:15:32,640
- Sit down.
- You have a nerve. Go fuck yourselves!

85
00:15:32,720 --> 00:15:34,880
- Sit down and stop swearing !
- Don't swear !

86
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:37,080
- Come on, Dad.
- Wait, it's OK.

87
00:15:37,760 --> 00:15:41,880
First of all, don't drag the Prophet's
name into your lies.

88
00:15:42,680 --> 00:15:44,880
We're country folk,
but we're not stupid.

89
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:46,560
You have another agenda.

90
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:50,760
I don't. All I want is to be buried
under the tree I planted as a boy.

91
00:15:51,040 --> 00:15:54,880
Second, this is the title deed
for Parcel No 54 in Zone 2.

92
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:57,600
- So what ?
- The tree is in Zone 3.

93
00:15:58,760 --> 00:16:02,160
The back wall of the prayer room is
the boundary. Can you let me past ?

94
00:16:02,520 --> 00:16:04,800
We own the whole of Parcel No 54.

95
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:08,560
You've got mixed up.
You planted the tree somewhere else.

96
00:16:08,680 --> 00:16:10,920
I know exactly where
I planted the tree.

97
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:14,920
My friend, take your father away
before things get nasty.

98
00:16:15,040 --> 00:16:17,240
- Bring the title deed and we'll talk.
- You have it !

99
00:16:17,320 --> 00:16:19,800
Screw that !
He told you to get out, OK ?

100
00:16:19,920 --> 00:16:23,560
Fuck off ! Shit-for-brains !
Sit down there !

101
00:16:26,520 --> 00:16:27,640
Asshole !

102
00:16:27,760 --> 00:16:29,200
- Wait !
- Come on, Dad !

103
00:16:29,280 --> 00:16:32,560
- The title deed's right here.
- Go on, mister. Out of here.

104
00:16:34,600 --> 00:16:36,720
God give me strength !

105
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:41,040
Get me some tea, nephew.

106
00:16:58,160 --> 00:16:59,720
What are you trying to do ?

107
00:17:00,640 --> 00:17:02,880
What you did back there
was shameful, Dad.

108
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:06,120
You ask me to bring you
to the village. I bring you.

109
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:08,520
You say they won't bury you
where you want.

110
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:11,240
So I drop everything
and come here with you.

111
00:17:11,520 --> 00:17:13,720
I think maybe you have regrets.

112
00:17:13,880 --> 00:17:17,480
But I see no fucking sign of regret.
Why are you like this, Dad ?

113
00:17:18,840 --> 00:17:21,240
Why does the world
have to revolve around you ?

114
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:24,640
What makes you so great ?
What makes you so great, Dad ?

115
00:17:25,960 --> 00:17:27,960
You don't give a fuck about anything !

116
00:17:28,040 --> 00:17:31,400
Why go after the guys' holy place ?
What the fuck is Noah Tree anyway ?

117
00:17:31,520 --> 00:17:32,960
What is Noah Tree ?

118
00:17:33,040 --> 00:17:36,080
We came all this way.
Why didn't you tell me any of this ?

119
00:17:36,720 --> 00:17:38,920
What kind of a man are you, Dad ?

120
00:17:39,040 --> 00:17:42,200
Then you turn up with a title deed
like you're tricking a kid.

121
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:45,840
What's wrong with you, man ?

122
00:17:45,960 --> 00:17:49,160
OK, you're sick. Everyone's sick.
Mum was sick, too.

123
00:17:49,320 --> 00:17:50,880
Everyone has stuff going on.

124
00:17:50,960 --> 00:17:52,960
Do you have any idea
what I'm going through ?

125
00:17:53,040 --> 00:17:55,040
I'm going through a divorce.

126
00:17:56,920 --> 00:17:58,560
Motherfuckers !

127
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:55,360
Sons of bitches !

128
00:21:56,520 --> 00:21:58,880
- What's wrong ?
- What the fuck is this ?

129
00:21:59,040 --> 00:22:01,560
Motherfucking sons of bitches !

130
00:22:03,480 --> 00:22:06,120
See what the fuckers have done.

131
00:22:08,800 --> 00:22:10,760
Selam aleykum.
What's going on ?

132
00:22:11,560 --> 00:22:12,960
Look at this.

133
00:22:13,080 --> 00:22:15,880
Like you need to ask !
They've wrecked the fucking house.

134
00:22:16,240 --> 00:22:17,880
God damn them !

135
00:22:18,840 --> 00:22:20,440
That's too bad.

136
00:22:20,640 --> 00:22:22,800
I'm the local imam.
I came to wish you welcome.

137
00:22:22,880 --> 00:22:25,880
Thanks.
They've wrecked the place, look.

138
00:22:25,960 --> 00:22:28,480
Forgive them.
They don't know what they're doing.

139
00:22:28,560 --> 00:22:32,200
They know damn well. It was deliberate.
This wasn't kids' doing.

140
00:22:32,360 --> 00:22:35,520
They left shit all over the place.
It was totally deliberate.

141
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:37,400
Who did it ?

142
00:22:37,880 --> 00:22:39,720
I don't know. God forbid !

143
00:22:39,800 --> 00:22:42,440
But I've heard
what you said about the tree.

144
00:22:42,520 --> 00:22:43,640
What ?

145
00:22:43,720 --> 00:22:46,960
It's willful ignorance.
Why would the Ark be here, right ?

146
00:22:47,040 --> 00:22:48,800
I've said so, but they
won't believe me either.

147
00:22:48,880 --> 00:22:50,640
In the end, someone
must have planted that tree.

148
00:22:50,720 --> 00:22:52,040
Exactly.

149
00:22:52,240 --> 00:22:54,480
Is there a hose ? I'll help clean up.

150
00:22:55,160 --> 00:22:56,880
The water isn't connected yet.

151
00:22:56,960 --> 00:22:59,840
- I'll take care of that.
- I'll stick that hose up their asses.

152
00:22:59,960 --> 00:23:03,480
- Anyway, I'm Ahmet.
- Ibrahim. And Ömer, my son.

153
00:23:04,640 --> 00:23:07,040
This is my family's honey.
From Kars.

154
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:10,400
I hope you like it.

155
00:23:10,640 --> 00:23:12,160
Just look at this.

156
00:23:33,960 --> 00:23:36,160
His father was
the village head, too.

157
00:23:38,640 --> 00:23:41,280
They'd stop at nothing
for a little bit of land.

158
00:23:44,240 --> 00:23:45,840
We packed and left.

159
00:24:11,800 --> 00:24:13,520
How did you two meet ?

160
00:24:15,800 --> 00:24:18,680
Your wife.
Where did you meet her ?

161
00:24:22,560 --> 00:24:24,160
On the cancer ward.

162
00:24:24,920 --> 00:24:26,560
She's a nurse ?

163
00:24:26,760 --> 00:24:29,600
- Her mum had cancer, too.
- I see.

164
00:24:35,240 --> 00:24:36,520
What's her name ?

165
00:24:38,280 --> 00:24:41,880
- What's her name ?
- Forget that. Just tell me this.

166
00:24:42,120 --> 00:24:45,800
The land that tree is on,
are you sure your family owns it ?

167
00:24:47,480 --> 00:24:50,000
- Yes, of course.
- Well, okay then.

168
00:24:50,800 --> 00:24:53,920
We'll clear this up in a day or two.
It won't take long.

169
00:24:56,720 --> 00:24:58,040
Let's go.

170
00:25:21,400 --> 00:25:23,680
I understand,
I've just been there, sir.

171
00:25:23,760 --> 00:25:25,680
But the gendarme commander
sent me here

172
00:25:25,840 --> 00:25:28,280
saying it comes
under police jurisdiction.

173
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:31,600
And now you're saying the opposite.
What do I do ?

174
00:25:31,800 --> 00:25:34,880
This is just a half-assed complaint.
Don't do this to me, please !

175
00:25:34,960 --> 00:25:37,640
These things happen a lot
in the countryside.

176
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:41,280
Villagers have their own way of life.

177
00:25:41,600 --> 00:25:44,040
- It's best not to interfere too much.
- OK, I get it.

178
00:25:45,480 --> 00:25:47,880
Honey, careful. You'll fall.

179
00:25:49,960 --> 00:25:51,320
How did it go ?

180
00:25:52,160 --> 00:25:53,680
I just don't get it.

181
00:25:53,880 --> 00:25:57,000
They say it's a disputed land
or something.

182
00:25:57,160 --> 00:25:58,760
- Let's have your ID.
- What for ?

183
00:25:58,840 --> 00:26:01,640
The land registry will know
who has jurisdiction.

184
00:26:01,880 --> 00:26:05,040
Forget the trespassing thing.
What's done is done.

185
00:26:06,680 --> 00:26:08,760
What's going on ?
The police were the same.

186
00:26:08,880 --> 00:26:11,560
Forget it ? Why ? Forget what ?

187
00:26:11,680 --> 00:26:13,440
They'll pay for what they did.

188
00:26:13,720 --> 00:26:17,160
Whatever you've done, you pay for it.
For God's sake !

189
00:26:17,480 --> 00:26:19,320
Great world we live in.

190
00:26:38,200 --> 00:26:41,440
Our inspectors will come
to the village on the 23rd.

191
00:26:41,720 --> 00:26:44,200
The 23rd ? Can't they come earlier ?

192
00:26:44,320 --> 00:26:46,360
- I'm afraid not.
- Oh no !

193
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:11,160
Mister, can you hear me ?
Move back !

194
00:27:12,480 --> 00:27:15,800
Breathe deeply. Deep breaths.
Can you hear me ?

195
00:27:17,880 --> 00:27:19,560
Have you called an ambulance ?

196
00:27:52,680 --> 00:27:54,400
Sorry to hear about your old man.

197
00:27:55,080 --> 00:27:57,120
I hope he's recovering well.

198
00:27:57,840 --> 00:28:00,840
- Things sure get around fast here.
- It's a small village.

199
00:28:02,480 --> 00:28:05,440
I'll pray for the old man
after evening prayers, God willing.

200
00:28:05,520 --> 00:28:06,640
Amen.

201
00:28:07,680 --> 00:28:09,640
Selam aleykum. How are you ?

202
00:28:09,760 --> 00:28:12,440
- Just fine.
- Praise be ! He looks good.

203
00:28:12,960 --> 00:28:15,880
We have to put on one of the patches
the hospital gave you.

204
00:28:16,120 --> 00:28:19,960
What patches ? I'm not in pain.
Come and have something to eat.

205
00:28:22,800 --> 00:28:25,680
- Have some braised meat, Ahmet.
- Not for me, thanks.

206
00:28:26,080 --> 00:28:28,040
But it's very good.

207
00:28:28,640 --> 00:28:31,280
- I don't eat meat.
- Really ? Why ?

208
00:28:33,320 --> 00:28:34,880
Long story.

209
00:28:36,040 --> 00:28:38,120
Hello ? Give me a second.

210
00:28:38,720 --> 00:28:42,240
Wait, Hülya. There's no signal here.
I'll call you right back.

211
00:28:42,520 --> 00:28:45,480
I'm going somewhere I can get a signal.
I'll be back soon.

212
00:28:45,600 --> 00:28:48,640
Go that way, towards the field.
You'll get a signal there.

213
00:28:51,400 --> 00:28:54,280
- Here.
- Thanks, that's great.

214
00:29:04,920 --> 00:29:07,680
Yes, sir. OK, I'll do that.

215
00:29:11,280 --> 00:29:14,000
The archive for that area
was damaged in the flood.

216
00:29:14,120 --> 00:29:17,280
What flood ? No one told my dad
anything about a flood.

217
00:29:17,560 --> 00:29:20,360
The building was apparently flooded.

218
00:29:20,440 --> 00:29:23,400
Before my time here.
A big part of the archive was damaged.

219
00:29:23,560 --> 00:29:26,680
- Which part ?
- The Noah Tree and surrounding area.

220
00:29:26,840 --> 00:29:29,120
The Noah Tree and surrounding area ?

221
00:29:30,520 --> 00:29:34,600
I'll get on your case, I warn you.
Believe me, it won't be pretty.

222
00:29:34,840 --> 00:29:37,000
Are you fucking with me ?
What is this ?

223
00:29:37,680 --> 00:29:42,520
Falsifying official documents,
withholding, altering or damaging them.

224
00:29:42,920 --> 00:29:45,200
They're all crimes.
You know that, don't you ?

225
00:29:45,280 --> 00:29:48,440
Don't go there.
You'll be in serious shit, I warn you.

226
00:29:48,560 --> 00:29:50,920
Tell your manager I'll be back
on Monday. You hear ?

227
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:53,560
I'll be here on Monday.
Fuckers !

228
00:30:00,680 --> 00:30:02,680
Selam aleykum, fellows.

229
00:30:20,680 --> 00:30:22,120
Could I have a tea ?

230
00:30:31,680 --> 00:30:33,280
Thanks.

231
00:30:36,080 --> 00:30:37,840
Remember me ?

232
00:31:36,560 --> 00:31:39,120
Why do you want to be buried
under that tree ?

233
00:31:43,920 --> 00:31:45,920
Sorry if I crossed the line here.

234
00:31:47,760 --> 00:31:50,120
You've never wanted
anything so badly ?

235
00:31:51,320 --> 00:31:56,240
I mean, something you wanted badly
without knowing why.

236
00:31:57,160 --> 00:32:01,360
I think rather than what we want,
how we want it is more important.

237
00:32:03,920 --> 00:32:07,560
I'd be skeptical of anything that's not
what both heart and mind desire.

238
00:32:07,640 --> 00:32:09,560
Skeptical, huh ?

239
00:32:12,640 --> 00:32:15,120
I trust my heart completely.

240
00:32:17,040 --> 00:32:19,480
In fact, I'd die if I stopped wanting.

241
00:32:20,240 --> 00:32:22,280
May God put off that day.

242
00:32:23,080 --> 00:32:25,920
- Have you fixed it ?
- It was exhausting.

243
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:29,200
I don't know if it'll work.

244
