Forgive me.

487
00:54:28,000 --> 00:54:29,880
Anyway, my point is this.

488
00:54:31,520 --> 00:54:36,120
Your father could well pass away soon,
though may God put off the day.

489
00:54:37,040 --> 00:54:40,280
You'll leave the village
and never come back. I know it.

490
00:54:41,280 --> 00:54:43,040
You're having a child.

491
00:54:43,920 --> 00:54:47,800
I heard. I was also sorry to hear
you're getting divorced.

492
00:54:48,920 --> 00:54:50,840
You'll have a lot of expenses.

493
00:54:51,640 --> 00:54:57,200
So let me give you half the money
in the account we opened for the tree.

494
00:54:58,760 --> 00:55:00,840
It's a sizeable sum.

495
00:55:01,320 --> 00:55:03,720
Make a nice life for yourself.

496
00:55:03,840 --> 00:55:06,000
Buy nice things for your child.

497
00:55:06,080 --> 00:55:10,160
Go and buy yourself
a nice house in Istanbul. Make a home.

498
00:55:11,840 --> 00:55:17,440
But just leave this village and the
Noah Tree alone, my friend. Please !

499
00:55:22,400 --> 00:55:24,040
You think it over, OK ?

500
00:55:26,840 --> 00:55:28,720
Goodbye and God bless !

501
00:56:39,200 --> 00:56:40,600
Look.

502
00:56:40,880 --> 00:56:44,560
I planned to use this thing to cut a
wedge from the tree. For the age rings.

503
00:56:44,960 --> 00:56:48,360
I wanted to show you the tree's age,
but then I couldn't do it.

504
00:56:50,200 --> 00:56:52,920
- You couldn't do it ?
- No. They say it can kill a tree.

505
00:56:54,200 --> 00:56:57,240
Dad, why bother with this stuff ?
It doesn't matter anymore.

506
00:56:57,360 --> 00:56:59,000
It does. It does to me.

507
00:57:00,200 --> 00:57:02,560
Do you believe I planted the tree ?

508
00:57:02,760 --> 00:57:06,760
Look, Dad. Isn't the land yours ?
Isn't it owned by your family ?

509
00:57:06,840 --> 00:57:09,640
The tree is yours, too.
You can do what you like with it.

510
00:57:09,760 --> 00:57:11,800
Do you believe I planted it or not ?

511
00:57:21,120 --> 00:57:23,240
Shall I put some more wood on ?

512
00:58:02,120 --> 00:58:03,400
Hello ?

513
00:58:03,560 --> 00:58:07,080
Hello. I was looking for Ömer.
They directed me to this house.

514
00:58:08,200 --> 00:58:09,720
Yes ?

515
00:58:09,920 --> 00:58:11,560
Are you his father ?

516
00:58:12,680 --> 00:58:14,280
Yes.

517
00:58:14,920 --> 00:58:19,200
He said such bad things about you.
I always pictured you as a monster.

518
00:58:20,240 --> 00:58:22,320
Turns out I'm human, though, huh ?

519
00:58:22,680 --> 00:58:25,480
I always believe the opposite of
anything Ömer says.

520
00:58:26,040 --> 00:58:27,520
I'm Elif.

521
00:58:27,600 --> 00:58:29,920
- Ömer's ex-wife.
- Ibrahim. Nice to meet you.

522
00:58:30,000 --> 00:58:31,680
You, too.

523
00:58:32,880 --> 00:58:35,920
Of course, he didn't tell you
he'd soon be a father either.

524
00:58:37,040 --> 00:58:38,640
He likes secrets.

525
00:58:51,080 --> 00:58:52,640
Elif ?

526
00:58:55,560 --> 00:58:57,640
You must have things to talk about.

527
00:58:57,800 --> 00:59:00,760
- It's OK by me. You can stay.
- No, no. I was going to...

528
00:59:01,640 --> 00:59:03,440
I'll go and do that now.

529
00:59:07,120 --> 00:59:09,320
So, how are you doing ?

530
00:59:10,000 --> 00:59:12,360
- Fine.
- Have a seat. Or we can...

531
00:59:12,480 --> 00:59:13,880
No need.

532
00:59:14,000 --> 00:59:16,080
Let's sit through there.
It's warmer.

533
00:59:17,160 --> 00:59:18,440
OK.

534
00:59:33,040 --> 00:59:34,640
Is it warm enough ?

535
00:59:35,440 --> 00:59:37,400
- I can put more wood on.
- No.

536
00:59:42,200 --> 00:59:45,480
- Have a seat.
- No, I have someone waiting.

537
00:59:47,280 --> 00:59:48,880
Who's the someone ?

538
00:59:50,600 --> 00:59:51,920
My boyfriend.

539
00:59:55,320 --> 00:59:57,600
- Your boyfriend ?
- Why not ?

540
01:00:00,520 --> 01:00:01,920
You're kidding.

541
01:00:05,320 --> 01:00:06,720
What boyfriend ?

542
01:00:07,720 --> 01:00:09,880
You know I'm slow at these things.

543
01:00:09,960 --> 01:00:14,520
Besides, what would anyone want
with a woman so pregnant ?

544
01:00:18,120 --> 01:00:19,680
How did you get here ?

545
01:00:20,680 --> 01:00:22,320
- By car.
- By car.

546
01:00:25,000 --> 01:00:26,800
But who told you I was here ?

547
01:00:27,800 --> 01:00:29,840
Ömer, isn't why I'm here
more important ?

548
01:00:30,320 --> 01:00:34,120
No. That you're here is important.
That you're standing here now.

549
01:00:37,120 --> 01:00:38,560
Have a seat.

550
01:00:39,280 --> 01:00:41,560
Water ? Tea ?
Can I get you a tea ?

551
01:00:51,880 --> 01:00:53,360
'The Idiot', huh ?

552
01:00:53,760 --> 01:00:55,360
Finally.

553
01:00:55,440 --> 01:00:57,720
Yes. I finished it.

554
01:00:58,280 --> 01:00:59,760
Good.

555
01:01:04,160 --> 01:01:06,960
- Ömer, why are you here ?
- How do you mean ?

556
01:01:10,200 --> 01:01:12,480
Isn't this the man
you conveniently blame

557
01:01:12,560 --> 01:01:15,560
for everything that's gone wrong
in your life ?

558
01:01:17,680 --> 01:01:20,760
Didn't you even try to pin
our failed relationship on him ?

559
01:01:22,080 --> 01:01:24,200
- It's those looks again.
- What looks ?

560
01:01:24,280 --> 01:01:26,320
Those judging looks.

561
01:01:30,320 --> 01:01:32,920
I guess I miss them. Even them.

562
01:01:37,240 --> 01:01:38,800
My dad's dying, Elif.

563
01:01:40,840 --> 01:01:42,680
I'm here to bury him.

564
01:01:44,240 --> 01:01:47,200
There's a place he wants to be buried.
It's a bit problematic.

565
01:01:49,240 --> 01:01:52,640
He can't handle it all alone.
I have to be here for him. He needs me.

566
01:01:54,680 --> 01:01:57,040
Shall I tell you why
you're really here ?

567
01:01:58,600 --> 01:02:00,000
Go on, tell me.

568
01:02:02,400 --> 01:02:06,640
You'd rather express your hate
than come into an unimaginable fortune.

569
01:02:09,600 --> 01:02:12,000
You're only here to pity your dad,

570
01:02:12,080 --> 01:02:15,920
to enjoy pitying him,
to express your hate, that's all.

571
01:02:17,320 --> 01:02:20,560
Doesn't that also explain
your sudden surge of paternal feeling ?

572
01:02:20,880 --> 01:02:22,520
What explains it ?

573
01:02:24,600 --> 01:02:25,920
You know what ?

574
01:02:26,840 --> 01:02:29,160
You wouldn't do anything
for anyone else

575
01:02:29,240 --> 01:02:31,800
unless there is something
in it for you.

576
01:02:32,520 --> 01:02:34,040
You couldn't.

577
01:02:38,160 --> 01:02:39,840
Why are you being so hard ?

578
01:02:40,960 --> 01:02:42,720
Why are you so pushy ?

579
01:02:43,800 --> 01:02:46,000
Why are you always telling
me what to do ?

580
01:02:46,600 --> 01:02:48,720
Why are you telling me how to act ?

581
01:02:49,360 --> 01:02:53,080
Can't you just let go ?
Accept me as I am. Please !

582
01:02:54,440 --> 01:02:57,240
Do you realize
you're always telling me what to do ?

583
01:02:57,760 --> 01:02:59,320
Stop !

584
01:02:59,400 --> 01:03:02,920
Sometimes I can't bring myself
to do things you want me to do

585
01:03:03,040 --> 01:03:07,320
just because you've told me
to do them. And I don't.

586
01:03:08,640 --> 01:03:10,960
Don't you realize that, Elif ?

587
01:03:11,560 --> 01:03:14,000
I always feel like
I'm doing everything wrong

588
01:03:14,080 --> 01:03:17,160
I'm so tired of wondering
what it is I'm doing wrong this time.

589
01:03:17,240 --> 01:03:20,680
I can't tell you how bad that feels,
Elif.

590
01:03:27,160 --> 01:03:29,480
- OK, Ömer. Enough.
- No !

591
01:03:29,600 --> 01:03:32,960
- We're not done. I want to talk.
- Really ?

592
01:03:34,360 --> 01:03:36,280
Then answer me this:

593
01:03:36,520 --> 01:03:39,400
Who's going to breastfeed the baby
when it's born. You ?

594
01:03:39,480 --> 01:03:41,480
Did I say that, for God's sake ?

595
01:03:41,560 --> 01:03:44,080
Then tell your lawyer
not to file for custody.

596
01:03:44,200 --> 01:03:45,640
- She will.
- What ?

597
01:03:45,720 --> 01:03:47,360
She will !

598
01:03:49,760 --> 01:03:52,720
This is the only thing in my life
that's been mine.

599
01:03:52,880 --> 01:03:55,000
I won't let you snatch it
away from me.

600
01:03:57,120 --> 01:04:00,600
This child will admire me.
I want her to admire me.

601
01:04:01,680 --> 01:04:04,040
What are you talking about ?
You're being truly ridiculous.

602
01:04:04,360 --> 01:04:06,400
Please talk to your lawyer.

603
01:04:06,720 --> 01:04:10,680
And by the way, that Hülya
fancies you. Take it from me.

604
01:04:11,480 --> 01:04:13,000
What ?

605
01:04:13,240 --> 01:04:15,040
Hülya fancies...

606
01:04:16,720 --> 01:04:19,400
OK. Really, that's enough.
Talk to your lawyer.

607
01:04:20,480 --> 01:04:23,160
These aren't things
to be discussed in a hurry.

608
01:04:23,920 --> 01:04:26,120
Please, Elif. Sit down.
I'm begging you.

609
01:04:26,480 --> 01:04:29,880
Let's make tea. Let's have tea.
Let's talk. Let's look at one another.

610
01:04:30,000 --> 01:04:31,280
OK.

611
01:04:31,400 --> 01:04:34,120
- Great !
- There, I'm sitting down.

612
01:04:34,680 --> 01:04:36,880
So, let's talk. What about ?

613
01:04:37,320 --> 01:04:39,360
What's left to talk about ?

614
01:04:39,880 --> 01:04:41,960
Ömer, what's left to talk about ?

615
01:04:43,200 --> 01:04:44,880
Please. Don't do this.

616
01:04:45,200 --> 01:04:47,160
If you care at all,

617
01:04:48,600 --> 01:04:51,360
keep the baby out of
your issues with the past.

618
01:04:54,040 --> 01:04:58,280
Surprise me just for once.
Please !

619
01:05:01,800 --> 01:05:05,400
- One day you'll apologize to me, Elif.
- Why's that ?

620
01:05:06,240 --> 01:05:08,320
You'll apologize to me.

621
01:05:11,120 --> 01:05:12,880
I can see it in your eyes.

622
01:05:14,920 --> 01:05:18,280
You'll apologize to me.
For everything you've done to me.

623
01:05:19,320 --> 01:05:21,800
You'll apologize
for making me like this.

624
01:05:22,360 --> 01:05:26,720
I put you at the center of my life.
You'll apologize for not staying there.

625
01:05:28,000 --> 01:05:30,760
Our relationship could've been
in a very different place.

626
01:05:30,840 --> 01:05:33,040
You'll apologize for not allowing it.

627
01:05:33,520 --> 01:05:35,920
You'll apologize for
making me a man you hate

628
01:05:36,120 --> 01:05:37,800
when you could've loved me.

629
01:05:39,280 --> 01:05:43,200
You'll apologize for taking that ring
off your finger so fast, Elif.

630
01:05:49,200 --> 01:05:51,000
You know what I'll do then ?

631
01:05:51,960 --> 01:05:53,920
I'll accept all your apologies.

632
01:05:54,440 --> 01:05:56,280
Because that's the way I am.

633
01:05:59,520 --> 01:06:01,400
I told you something, remember ?

634
01:06:04,280 --> 01:06:07,360
My tolerance will save
our relationship, Elif.

635
01:07:01,160 --> 01:07:02,880
Can I have a word with you ?

636
01:07:10,320 --> 01:07:13,440
Surely a grown man doesn't
need permission to speak to me.

637
01:07:14,160 --> 01:07:16,720
- We can talk right there.
- OK.

638
01:08:50,560 --> 01:08:52,000
Son of a...

639
01:08:54,680 --> 01:08:56,600
So stubborn...

640
01:08:58,240 --> 01:09:00,240
- I found this.
- Good.

641
01:09:00,920 --> 01:09:02,440
It's stuck.

642
01:09:11,560 --> 01:09:12,720
Take these.

643
01:09:12,840 --> 01:09:14,880
- I guess that's enough.
- Thanks.

644
01:09:15,240 --> 01:09:17,120
My back hurts anyway.

645
01:09:18,480 --> 01:09:20,160
- Dad.
- Huh ?

646
01:09:20,760 --> 01:09:24,040
- What did you and Elif talk about ?
- She just apologized.

647
01:09:24,680 --> 01:09:25,840
- She apologized ?
- Yes.

648
01:09:25,920 --> 01:09:28,280
- Why ?
- She called me a monster, remember ?

649
01:09:30,440 --> 01:09:32,880
- You didn't talk about anything else ?
- No.

650
01:09:33,040 --> 01:09:35,080
You seemed to be talking for longer.

651
01:09:35,200 --> 01:09:38,480
Well, there was the before and after,
nothing to speak of.

652
01:09:39,240 --> 01:09:43,520
Just the usual civilities,
"How are you ?" and so on, that's all.

653
01:09:46,800 --> 01:09:48,480
Dad, leave it there.
I'll take it in.

654
01:09:48,560 --> 01:09:50,680
- No, it's OK.
- I have more to chop anyway.

655
01:09:50,800 --> 01:09:52,320
It's fine.

656
01:09:55,160 --> 01:09:56,360
OK.

657
01:09:59,560 --> 01:10:01,880
OK. I see.

658
01:10:05,120 --> 01:10:07,120
But who wants those documents ?

659
01:10:07,880 --> 01:10:10,520
No, I mean why do they want them ?
Is it the court ?

660
01:10:11,640 --> 01:10:13,320
OK, I'll handle it.

661
01:10:14,440 --> 01:10:16,000
I'll take care of it.

662
01:10:19,560 --> 01:10:21,800
Hülya, can I call you back later ?

663
01:10:22,680 --> 01:10:26,280
The land registry guys are here.
I'll call you back. OK, bye.

664
01:10:54,440 --> 01:10:56,160
What's going on ?

665
01:10:56,400 --> 01:10:58,560
What the hell is this ?

666
01:11:01,640 --> 01:11:04,520
Was it you who sent the officers away ?
Fuck you !

667
01:11:04,880 --> 01:11:07,040
Get out of here !
Fuck-faces ! Fuck you !

668
01:11:33,320 --> 01:11:34,640
Ömer !

669
01:11:36,080 --> 01:11:37,440
- Fuck !
- Son, are you OK ?

670
01:11:37,520 --> 01:11:40,280
Dad, what are you doing there ?
Get out of the way !

671
01:11:41,560 --> 01:11:43,480
Fuckers ! Break it all, fuckers !

672
01:11:43,920 --> 01:11:46,640
Break it all, motherfuckers !
Sons of bitches !

673
01:11:48,680 --> 01:11:50,280
Fucking bastards !

674
01:11:57,280 --> 01:11:58,800
No, there's no one here.

675
01:12:07,960 --> 01:12:10,120
- Where are you going ?
- To cut down the tree.

676
01:12:10,240 --> 01:12:11,680
No, don't !

677
01:12:13,200 --> 01:12:15,240
Ömer ! Don't do it !

678
01:12:15,560 --> 01:12:18,120
- No, this shit has to end tonight.
- Don't do it.

679
01:12:18,400 --> 01:12:20,840
- Fuck that tree.
- Don't. Don't touch their tree.

680
01:12:20,920 --> 01:12:22,800
Touch whose tree ? The tree's yours,
Dad !

681
01:12:22,880 --> 01:12:25,080
No, no.
I don't want the tree anymore.

682
01:12:25,680 --> 01:12:28,440
That's over. I gave up.

683
01:12:29,800 --> 01:12:32,120
Ömer, don't.
They'll do something to you.

684
01:12:32,200 --> 01:12:34,200
Don't cut it down, Ömer !

685
01:12:34,520 --> 01:12:36,600
Son ! Don't !

686
01:12:38,360 --> 01:12:41,800
You'll get in trouble because of me !
Don't ! Ömer !

687
01:12:43,040 --> 01:12:44,520
Ömer, don't !

688
01:12:55,800 --> 01:12:57,960
Dad ?
Dad, are you OK ?

689
01:13:01,320 --> 01:13:03,880
What shall we do, Dad ?
What shall I do ?

690
01:13:04,520 --> 01:13:07,080
It's OK. I'll be fine.

691
01:13:19,280 --> 01:13:21,240
This soup is looking good.

692
01:13:21,600 --> 01:13:24,640
Dad, it's freezing in here.
I'm closing this, OK ?

693
01:13:24,760 --> 01:13:26,640
- OK.
- That's enough air.

694
01:13:31,560 --> 01:13:33,240
You know what ?

695
01:13:35,200 --> 01:13:37,400
There was a rock by the tree
I planted.

696
01:13:39,360 --> 01:13:41,440
I've looked,
but can't see a rock there.

697
01:13:43,560 --> 01:13:45,560
I don't think it's the tree I planted.

698
01:13:46,440 --> 01:13:49,200
For God's sake, Dad !
No rock hangs around for 50 years.

699
01:13:50,880 --> 01:13:54,440
Anyway they put that prayer room there.
The rock could be underneath.

700
01:13:55,040 --> 01:13:57,680
Relax.
I'm not going to touch the tree.

701
01:14:05,200 --> 01:14:07,680
Bury me in the small cemetery.

702
01:14:12,960 --> 01:14:15,920
- Your soup will get cold.
- Never mind the soup.

703
01:14:16,440 --> 01:14:19,240
- OK ?
- Is what OK ?

704
01:14:19,560 --> 01:14:21,640
That you bury me
in the small cemetery.

705
01:14:21,920 --> 01:14:23,760
Dad, OK.
But do you have to pick now...

706
01:14:23,920 --> 01:14:25,920
Is that a real OK ?

707
01:14:28,440 --> 01:14:29,960
OK.

708
01:14:36,680 --> 01:14:39,840
When I was in Istanbul,
I visited your mother's grave.

709
01:14:41,680 --> 01:14:43,200
Before coming to you.

710
01:14:51,680 --> 01:14:53,680
I'm putting a lot of lemon in here,
OK ?

711
01:14:54,120 --> 01:14:56,840
I'll squeeze this one as well.
It'll be quite sour,

712
01:14:58,040 --> 01:15:01,360
but the bread will counter that.
I'll crumble the bread into it.

713
01:15:04,080 --> 01:15:06,240
You need to get this soup down.

714
01:15:09,040 --> 01:15:10,960
You'll be a good father.

715
01:15:23,160 --> 01:15:24,640
That's so weird.

716
01:15:32,120 --> 01:15:34,080
Mum said the same thing.

717
01:15:35,480 --> 01:15:38,120
She said the same thing
in the same circumstances.

718
01:15:40,360 --> 01:15:42,680
She said I'd be a good father.

719
01:15:44,760 --> 01:15:47,440
I'll be a good father, huh ?

720
01:15:51,560 --> 01:15:53,360
I won't be anything.

721
01:15:55,560 --> 01:15:57,600
- Huh ?
- I won't be anything.

722
01:16:01,160 --> 01:16:02,960
Why do you say that ?

723
01:16:12,880 --> 01:16:14,640
Eat your soup.

724
01:17:45,920 --> 01:17:47,960
Is he asleep or something ?

725
01:17:49,800 --> 01:17:51,720
- Selam aleykum.
- Aleykum selam.

726
01:17:51,840 --> 01:17:56,320
I've brought the window-man from town.
Let's get this lot fixed, my friend.

727
01:17:56,880 --> 01:18:00,040
- Thanks. There was no need, though.
- No, it's fine.

728
01:18:02,360 --> 01:18:03,920
Nihat is from the village.

729
01:19:32,600 --> 01:19:34,520
Shame on you. Assholes !

730
01:19:45,920 --> 01:19:47,200
Dad, are you OK ?

731
01:19:55,960 --> 01:19:57,320
Dad ?

732
01:20:05,520 --> 01:20:07,680
I had a car like this in France.

733
01:20:08,400 --> 01:20:10,400
Not quite the same, but...

734
01:20:11,280 --> 01:20:13,040
Are you happy with it ?

735
01:20:13,960 --> 01:20:16,320
- Sure, I guess I'm happy with it.
- It's a good car.

736
01:20:17,320 --> 01:20:21,640
- Are you feeling any better ?
- Fine, yes. Better. This helps.

737
01:20:23,080 --> 01:20:25,040
Look. Look over there.

738
01:20:25,360 --> 01:20:27,600
That's where we used
to play as kids.

739
01:20:29,360 --> 01:20:31,600
See that button ?
You can heat the seat.

740
01:20:31,840 --> 01:20:33,800
I've already switched it on.

741
01:20:34,120 --> 01:20:37,480
Look, they're both on.
But there's no one to sit there.

742
01:20:52,240 --> 01:20:56,200
Seeing as you have the heat on,
I'll come and get my ass warm.

743
01:20:58,200 --> 01:21:01,400
I thought about doing that, too,
but I didn't dare.

744
01:21:10,760 --> 01:21:14,680
Look... Mr. Tahsin and Mrs. Bedriye
used to live over there.

745
01:21:15,320 --> 01:21:16,800
It's a wreck now.

746
01:21:17,520 --> 01:21:19,120
Those were the days...

747
01:21:20,240 --> 01:21:22,240
- Are you hungry ?
- No, I'm fine.

748
01:21:22,600 --> 01:21:25,440
We can go find some soup if you like.

749
01:21:25,600 --> 01:21:29,560
- There'll be somewhere open, Dad.
- OK. We can have a look.

750
01:23:01,640 --> 01:23:03,000
Fuck !

751
01:23:03,560 --> 01:23:05,720
- What's the matter ?
- Something got into my eye.

752
01:23:10,160 --> 01:23:12,720
- The ceiling's falling down.
- That'll do.

753
01:23:12,840 --> 01:23:14,760
- It won't hold, though.
- It will.

754
01:23:14,960 --> 01:23:17,280
- Fine, give me that.
- Here.

755
01:23:26,600 --> 01:23:30,680
She said you're helping me here
to prove to me, to her and to yourself

756
01:23:30,840 --> 01:23:33,840
that you aren't a selfish person
like me.

757
01:23:34,840 --> 01:23:37,560
That's why you've come
to the village, she said.

758
01:23:40,280 --> 01:23:41,440
What ?

759
01:23:41,520 --> 01:23:44,320
And that's why
you want the child so badly.

760
01:23:45,440 --> 01:23:47,680
According to her,
that's totally selfish.

761
01:23:49,080 --> 01:23:53,200
She said you didn't even want the child
at first. You wanted an abortion.

762
01:23:53,320 --> 01:23:55,200
- I didn't want the child ?
- Uh-huh.

763
01:23:55,280 --> 01:23:57,320
- Did she really say that, Dad ?
- Yes.

764
01:23:57,400 --> 01:23:59,600
She said I didn't want the child ?

765
01:24:02,600 --> 01:24:04,560
I never said anything like that.

766
01:24:06,400 --> 01:24:07,560
Did I ?

767
01:24:14,400 --> 01:24:16,040
I never said that.

768
01:24:20,880 --> 01:24:22,720
It can't be that complicated.

769
01:24:23,160 --> 01:24:26,480
This didn't plant it. That didn't
plant it. So who the fuck did ?

770
01:24:27,040 --> 01:24:28,400
My Dad then.

771
01:24:28,520 --> 01:24:31,240
- That's what he says.
- OK, but why do you believe him ?

772
01:24:31,400 --> 01:24:33,280
He's always contradicting himself.

773
01:24:34,360 --> 01:24:36,920
The other day he said
he didn't care about the tree.

774
01:24:37,200 --> 01:24:38,720
Who knows ?

775
01:24:40,280 --> 01:24:43,800
Ibrahim is... an interesting man.
A complex man.

776
01:24:44,360 --> 01:24:46,120
I think he's afraid.

777
01:24:47,200 --> 01:24:49,240
He's afraid of the villagers.

778
01:24:50,480 --> 01:24:52,960
He's afraid they'll do something
to me.

779
01:24:53,800 --> 01:24:55,600
That's why he acts the way he does.

780
01:24:57,640 --> 01:25:01,440
Last summer I told the kids
that Noah's Ark never came here.

781
01:25:02,000 --> 01:25:05,320
Then the parents didn't send their kids
to Quran classes rest of the summer.

782
01:25:05,720 --> 01:25:08,800
I'm an imam.
It's my duty to share the truth.

783
01:25:10,280 --> 01:25:13,160
I also told the village council
when I first arrived.

784
01:25:13,280 --> 01:25:15,840
They told me to stop interpreting
the Quran arbitrarily.

785
01:25:15,920 --> 01:25:17,760
They ignored me.
I'll fix this.

786
01:25:19,840 --> 01:25:23,560
And I'm going to stick that title deed
up their asses.

787
01:25:25,360 --> 01:25:28,840
May God keep you from bad language.
Hey, you won't play with me ?

788
01:25:49,600 --> 01:25:53,840
They say everything was damaged
in the flood. The entire archive.

789
01:25:54,560 --> 01:25:57,040
That's not true.
There was hardly any damage.

790
01:25:57,240 --> 01:26:00,200
A couple of tons of coal
were damaged, that's all.

791
01:26:00,280 --> 01:26:01,760
- Coal ?
- Yes.

792
01:26:01,840 --> 01:26:05,040
- So the archive wasn't damaged ?
- No, there was no damage.

793
01:26:05,640 --> 01:26:07,400
Not as far as I know.

794
01:26:12,000 --> 01:26:14,600
- How much do you get paid ?
- Why do you want to know ?

795
01:26:18,040 --> 01:26:19,640
Thanks. You're a star.

796
01:26:21,920 --> 01:26:23,120
He's a great kid.

797
01:26:23,200 --> 01:26:25,360
- There you go, Dad.
- Thanks.

798
01:26:27,920 --> 01:26:29,920
- How old is he ?
- Ten.

799
01:26:31,360 --> 01:26:34,120
Don't worry,
I work in the public sector too.

800
01:26:34,840 --> 01:26:37,000
Just tell me how much you earn.

801
01:26:37,640 --> 01:26:39,200
Enough to get by.

802
01:26:40,320 --> 01:26:42,760
- The minimum wage.
- The minimum wage ?

803
01:26:45,640 --> 01:26:48,640
- Do you want to make some money ?
- How ?

804
01:26:51,280 --> 01:26:53,360
No, don't. Don't.

805
01:26:56,640 --> 01:26:58,360
Take it. Go on.

806
01:26:58,880 --> 01:27:01,760
Don't leave me hanging here.
Come on, take it.

807
01:27:02,160 --> 01:27:03,520
I'll explain in a second.

808
01:27:05,600 --> 01:27:07,120
So you know the archive ?

809
01:27:07,240 --> 01:27:10,960
Get me a copy of our title deed
from the archive. OK ?

810
01:27:11,080 --> 01:27:13,880
Get the copy and I'll give you
the same again. OK ?

811
01:27:35,440 --> 01:27:37,520
- You're back ?
- What's up ?

812
01:27:38,640 --> 01:27:40,360
Tayfun called.

813
01:27:41,200 --> 01:27:43,960
He mentioned a new drug,
some new procedure.

814
01:27:44,200 --> 01:27:48,080
He's used it on a few patients, says
it works well, halts growth and so on.

815
01:27:48,680 --> 01:27:51,080
- I'll be kept in for a few nights.
- Who's Tayfun ?

816
01:27:51,320 --> 01:27:53,680
My doctor. The one in Istanbul.

817
01:27:54,040 --> 01:27:56,280
- Isn't your doctor in France ?
- No.

818
01:27:56,960 --> 01:28:00,040
That's Pierre's friend.
Sure, he's in France, but Tayfun...

819
01:28:00,200 --> 01:28:02,440
- Didn't I tell you ?
- No.

820
01:28:02,520 --> 01:28:04,720
They went to graduate school together.

821
01:28:04,800 --> 01:28:07,280
He said to see him
when I was back in Turkey.

822
01:28:07,400 --> 01:28:09,880
Which I did before coming to you.

823
01:28:10,000 --> 01:28:13,280
He said I should give it a try,
that it could help a lot.

824
01:28:13,480 --> 01:28:15,720
- He'll try out the new drug ?
- Uh- huh.

825
01:28:18,120 --> 01:28:20,480
- That's great.
- Isn't it ?

826
01:28:22,320 --> 01:28:24,200
That's fantastic news, Dad.

827
01:28:24,680 --> 01:28:28,000
- Let's go now.
- Not on the country roads at night.

828
01:28:28,320 --> 01:28:30,560
There's no need.
We'll go in the morning.

829
01:28:31,240 --> 01:28:33,720
OK, fine. I'll go and pack a bag.

830
01:28:36,280 --> 01:28:40,560
- OK. Let's have something to eat.
- OK. I'm all done here anyway.

831
01:28:51,560 --> 01:28:53,280
Look after the dog, OK ?

832
01:29:01,520 --> 01:29:05,200
Let me give you this, too.
You can give the meat to someone else.

833
01:29:06,840 --> 01:29:09,120
OK. I'll take care of it. Thanks.

834
01:29:15,320 --> 01:29:18,000
I'll be back in the morning
to see you off.

835
01:29:21,280 --> 01:29:23,160
- Good night.
- Good night.

836
01:30:26,560 --> 01:30:28,920
Hey, boy. What happened to you ?

837
01:30:30,000 --> 01:30:31,800
What happened to you, handsome ?

838
01:30:35,320 --> 01:30:36,920
Who tied you up here ?

839
01:30:37,720 --> 01:30:39,840
Wait, handsome. Let's untie you.

840
01:32:05,320 --> 01:32:07,560
Come on, Cemal ! Let's go !

841
01:33:54,640 --> 01:33:57,280
Selam aleykum.
Have you seen my father ?

842
01:34:03,960 --> 01:34:05,360
Hilmi !

843
01:34:05,600 --> 01:34:07,360
Round everyone up !

844
01:34:08,360 --> 01:34:10,480
Let's check The Deep Valley.

845
01:34:11,440 --> 01:34:12,880
Let's go !

846
01:34:15,440 --> 01:34:17,640
I'm half-tempted not to bury Dad.

847
01:34:19,560 --> 01:34:22,280
To leave him to rot
in the living room at home.

848
01:34:22,840 --> 01:34:25,080
And let the whole village
reek of death.

849
01:34:27,320 --> 01:34:30,000
So that those assholes
can't sleep because of the reek.

850
01:34:32,000 --> 01:34:34,760
So that they remember
the outrage they committed.

851
01:34:34,880 --> 01:34:37,400
So that they feel guilty
every time they smell it.

852
01:34:39,320 --> 01:34:40,640
Sons of bitches.

853
01:34:41,360 --> 01:34:42,920
Sons of bitches.

854
01:34:43,800 --> 01:34:45,800
I'm not burying my Dad.

855
01:34:46,160 --> 01:34:48,240
I'll toss his body
into the living room,

856
01:34:48,600 --> 01:34:51,600
lock the doors and fuck off.
That's justice.

857
01:34:55,040 --> 01:34:57,160
We must leave justice to God, Ömer.

858
01:34:58,240 --> 01:35:00,120
What you said isn't right.

859
01:35:00,600 --> 01:35:02,440
Let's just find Ibrahim first.

860
01:35:03,160 --> 01:35:05,720
Then we can give him
a ritual burial, God willing.

861
01:35:08,760 --> 01:35:11,160
Maybe the villagers
did something to Ibrahim.

862
01:35:11,440 --> 01:35:13,160
No, what would they do ?

863
01:35:13,800 --> 01:35:16,960
- He tied up the dog and left.
- But why did he tie up the dog ?

864
01:35:18,480 --> 01:35:20,520
Why ? So it didn't follow him.

865
01:35:24,880 --> 01:35:27,680
Mr. Ömer, this is the last place
we'll be looking on land.

866
01:35:28,120 --> 01:35:30,160
I hope we'll have success.

867
01:35:31,720 --> 01:35:33,320
Carry on in line !

868
01:36:55,160 --> 01:36:58,880
- Yes ?
- So... I couldn't do it.

869
01:36:59,640 --> 01:37:01,360
I'm sorry.

870
01:37:02,280 --> 01:37:05,040
Sorry. I'm kind of dizzy.
Just a second.

871
01:37:07,400 --> 01:37:09,960
- It's OK. Keep it.
- No, out of the question.

872
01:37:10,080 --> 01:37:12,120
- It's OK. Keep it.
- No, I can't.

873
01:39:09,200 --> 01:39:11,320
- Hello.
- Hello ?

874
01:39:12,840 --> 01:39:14,200
Elif ?

875
01:39:14,360 --> 01:39:16,560
What's up, Ömer ?
You know what the time is ?

876
01:39:18,760 --> 01:39:20,400
Elif, Dad is dead.

877
01:39:26,880 --> 01:39:28,600
Come here, my dear.

878
01:39:30,360 --> 01:39:34,240
- It's okay. Come here, sweetie.
- Shall I take the baby, ma'am ?

879
01:39:34,760 --> 01:39:36,200
No.

880
01:39:47,440 --> 01:39:49,200
I'm sorry for your loss.

881
01:39:52,080 --> 01:39:54,360
Would you like us to come over ?

882
01:39:57,040 --> 01:39:58,680
Ömer ?

883
01:40:00,800 --> 01:40:02,520
Can you hear me ?

884
01:40:03,360 --> 01:40:04,960
Ömer...

885
01:42:08,200 --> 01:42:11,520
NOAH LAND

